data.enText: following immediately one after the other

data.chText: 这是他们连续第四次获胜。
data.enText: This was their fourth successive win.

data.chText: 历届政府都试图解决这个问题。
data.enText: Successive governments have tried to tackle the problem.

data.chText: 这一概念相继应用于绘画、建筑和雕塑中。
data.enText: This concept has been applied successively to painting, architecture and sculpture.

ex.chText: 他一直在不断地改写论文。
ex.enText: He is in a continual process of rewriting his paper.

ex.chText: 断断续续的炮火使我们彻夜未眠。
ex.enText: The continual gunfire kept us awake all night.

ex.chText: 频频的闪电吓坏了孩子。
ex.enText: The continual flashes of lightning scared the child.

synonyms.bx: 指不间断地长时间持续的，或令人厌烦地反复发生的，只作定语。

ex.chText: 大脑需要连续不断地供血。
ex.enText: The brain needs a continuous supply of blood.

ex.chText: 一周的连续轰炸使整个城市成了废墟。
ex.enText: A week's continuous bombing destroyed the whole city.

synonyms.bx: 语义最强，指在时间和空间上没有间断的，强调没有停顿或间歇。

ex.chText: 他在一场比赛中连续打出4个本垒打。
ex.enText: He hit four successive home runs in one game.

synonyms.bx: 指事物一个接一个地发生或到来的，期间没有间断，只作定语。

value.def: Successive means happening or existing one after another without a break.

example.ex: Jackson was the winner for a second successive year...
example.tran: 杰克逊已经是连续第二年获胜了。

example.ex: Britain was suffering from the failure of successive governments to co-ordinate a national transport policy.
example.tran: 接连几届政府都没能协调出一个全国性的交通运输政策，英国因此而深受其苦。

example.ex: He successively won the British, European and World championships.
example.tran: 他一口气拿下了英国、欧洲和世界冠军。

example.ex: ...the successively higher levels of unemployment we have endured during the past three recessions.
example.tran: 在过去三次大萧条中我们所经历的持续上涨的失业率
